Notes: Same link for all ceramic capacitors
Depending on what LEDs you get, they might be too bright and you’ll need bigger resistors for them

Ideally, you want 6*6mm tact switches with square heads, that will fit the cap nicely. If you want to only order from tayda, you can probably force the cap onto a round head switch, like this https://www.taydaelectronics.com/tact-switch-6-6mm-7-3mm-through-hole-spst-no.html
For the original illuminated buttons with 8mm head, you can get these ones https://www.aliexpress.com/item/4000415375387.html?gatewayAdapt=4itemAdapt

Depending on which buttons you use, you may have to do some light re-wiring by adding jumpers between certain pins. On the board, the two middle pins need to connect to the two bottom pins when the button is pressed.
Needs STM32F103CBT6 version, with 128kb memory. You can only get clones of these currently. I’m working on a smaller version of firmware to work on 64kb.
Not common on ali sites, since the output is not v/oct, it’s easiest to just replace it with a zener like this: https://www.taydaelectronics.com/1n4740a-1n4740-zener-diode-10v-1w.html
Can be found on ali sites, like here: https://www.aliexpress.com/item/33020375029.html
Some clone boards have a 5V pin at the top right, instead of the usual ground. Cut the pin off if it has 5V.
